// deploy/presets.custom.jsonc — OPTIONAL operator preset overlay.
//
// Copy this file to `deploy/presets.custom.jsonc` (gitignored) and edit it to
// override or add LLM presets WITHOUT editing the package. It is MERGED over
// the bundled catalogue (bp_router/llm/presets_catalog.jsonc) at first-boot
// seed:
//   - a custom entry whose `name` collides with a built-in WINS (replaces it),
//   - a new `name` is added.
//
// Consulted ONLY when seeding an empty `llm_presets` table (first boot, or
// after TRUNCATE llm_presets). After that, presets live in the DB and are
// admin-managed via /admin — editing this file does NOT retroactively change
// an already-seeded deployment.
//
// JSONC: `//` and `/* */` comments allowed; NO trailing commas. Each entry
// mirrors the `Preset` dataclass:
//   Required: name, provider, concrete_model, api_key_ref
//   Optional: description, min_user_level, default_temperature,
//             default_max_tokens, default_provider_options, api_key, base_url,
//             fallback_preset, max_retries
//   provider ∈ gemini | anthropic | openai | openai-embeddings |
//              openai-compatible | openai-compatible-embeddings
//   name must match ^[a-z][a-z0-9_-]{0,63}$ (lowercase, no dots).
//
// Default below is an EMPTY array → a no-op overlay (safe to leave as-is).
// Example (uncomment + adapt):
//   {
//     "name": "default",
//     "provider": "openai-compatible",
//     "concrete_model": "qwen3:32b",
//     "api_key_ref": "env://OPENAI_API_KEY",
//     "base_url": "http://ollama:11434/v1",
//     "description": "Local Qwen via Ollama — overrides the bundled default."
//   }
[
]
